Shuaa Capital Acquires Land to Build Jeddah Budget Hotel

-- B y   Z a i n a b   F a t t a h
-- 
2011-08-08T06:50:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/shuaa-capital-acquires-land-to-build-jeddah-budget-hotel.html
Shuaa Capital PSC (SHUAA) ’s Saudi Arabian
unit acquired land in Jeddah to build a 160 million riyals ($43
million) budget hotel as it seeks to take advantage of the
kingdom’s strong demand for hotels.  The hotel, which will have about 12,000 square meters of
space, will include 254 rooms and will be managed by Rotana
Hotel Management Corp., an investment bank controlled by Dubai’s
ruler said in an e-mailed statement today.  Shuaa didn’t disclose the value or the location of the land
in Jeddah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zainab Fattah in Dubai on 
 zfattah@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
